  • Method Details

    • main

      public static void main(String[] args)
      Creates implementation for abstract class or interface.
      Parameters:
      args - target class and output folder

      If two arguments provided: runs implement(Class, Path) with first argument as class name and second as folder for output file

      If three arguments provided and first is -jar: runs implementJar(Class, Path) with second argument as class name and third as path to destination .jar file

    • generateCode

      private static String generateCode(Class<?> token) throws info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException
      Generates code of implementation for abstract class or interface by its token.
      Parameters:
      token - Target class token
      Returns:
      String with implementation of classNameImpl which extends or implements className class where className is name of token
      Throws:
      info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException - if token is final or equals Enum.class or if token is private.
      Also passes exception of generateClass(Class)
